OL,3,CCould the Birmingham Balti become
OL,4,CUNESCO protected?
OL,6,FCould Birmingham's famous Balti dish
OL,7,Fbecome protected under UNESCO?
OL,9,FThat's what a number of restaurants in
OL,10,Fthe city are hoping for.
OL,12,FPart of Birmingham's Balti Triangle in
OL,13,Fthe south east of the city, the
OL,14,Fbusiness owners have applied for the
OL,15,Fdish to be enshrined under the
OL,16,Fgovernment's cultural heritage scheme.
OL,18,FThe balti scene has been operating in
OL,19,Fthe city for nearly 50 years,
OL,20,Foriginating in the mid 1970s.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G1/4
